<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 2:42PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Boulder
County through 315 PM MDT...
At 241 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Lyons, or 28 miles south of Fort Collins, moving
east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor plants is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Longmont, Lyons, Jamestown and Niwot.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
